race.comment: MIC DROP (7) made a dream return off a massive 537-day break, showing no rust when running them along and never looking back here. That was a terrific training performance and while the second-up run can sometimes bring them undone, it felt like the perfect pipe-opener. Plenty more to offer and a clear winning hope again. BOLD DESIGN (4) resumes after an eye-catching first prep where he looked the real deal. Has been kept ticking with two easy trials and maps to get the suck run in behind. Expect him to be in the finish fresh. ROTHO BRO (5) is a sharp fresh performer and has trialled well. NARCISSIST (1) is capable if the blinkers spark him up.
